  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-07-22",
    "date": "2004-10-01T20:02:06Z",
    "text": "Intelligent Vehicle Highway Safety Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a deduction from gross income for the cost, up to $1,000, of qualified intelligent vehicle systems property. Defines \"qualified intelligent systems property\" as any device installed by a motor vehicle manufacturer to enhance the safety or security of a driver, passenger, or load by, among other things, warning or informing a driver of dangerous driving conditions or by actively monitoring and adjusting driver workload. Terminates the deduction after 2010.\n\nExempts intelligent vehicle systems properties from the first $5,000 of the excise tax on heavy trucks and trailers sold at retail."
  },
